<li id="cite_note-50"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-50">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"> A. Mark Smith has determined that there were at least two translators, based on their facility with Arabic; the first, more experienced scholar began the translation at the beginning of Book One, and handed it off in the middle of Chapter Three of Book Three. <a href="#CITEREFSmith2001">Smith 2001</a> <b>91</b> Volume 1: Commentary and Latin text pp.xx-xxi. See also his 2006, 2008, 2010 translations.</span>
</li>
</ol></div></div>
