<li id="cite_note-Khalili-12"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-Khalili_12-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Khalili_12-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFAl-Khalili,_Jim2009" class="citation news cs1">Al-Khalili, Jim (4 January 2009). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/science/nature/7810846.stm">"The 'first true scientist'<span class="cs1-kern-right"></span>"</a>. <i>BBC News</i>. <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20150426041228/http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/science/nature/7810846.stm">Archived</a> from the original on 26 April 2015<span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">2 June</span> 2018</span>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=BBC+News&amp;rft.atitle=The+%27first+true+scientist%27&amp;rft.date=2009-01-04&amp;rft.au=Al-Khalili%2C+Jim&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fnews.bbc.co.uk%2F2%2Fhi%2Fscience%2Fnature%2F7810846.stm&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AIbn+al-Haytham" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-13"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-13">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><a href="#CITEREFSelin2008">Selin 2008</a>: "The three most recognizable Islamic contributors to meteorology were: the Alexandrian mathematician/ astronomer Ibn al-Haytham (Alhazen 965–1039), the Arab-speaking Persian physician Ibn Sina (Avicenna 980–1037), and the Spanish Moorish physician/jurist Ibn Rushd (Averroes; 1126–1198)." He has been dubbed the "father of modern optics" by the <a href="/wiki/UNESCO" title="UNESCO">UNESCO</a>. <link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite class="citation journal cs1 cs1-prop-long-vol"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=4YE3AAAAMAAJ">"Impact of Science on Society"</a>. <i>UNESCO</i>. 26–27: 140. 1976. <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20230205005719/https://books.google.com/books?id=4YE3AAAAMAAJ">Archived</a> from the original on 5 February 2023<span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">12 September</span> 2019</span>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=UNESCO&amp;rft.atitle=Impact+of+Science+on+Society&amp;rft.volume=26%E2%80%9327&amp;rft.pages=140&amp;rft.date=1976&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3D4YE3AAAAMAAJ&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AIbn+al-Haytham" class="Z3988"></span>.
<link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite class="citation web cs1"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20141001171116/http://www.light2015.org/Home/ScienceStories/1000-Years-of-Arabic-Optics.html">"International Year of Light – Ibn Al-Haytham and the Legacy of Arabic Optics"</a>. <i>www.light2015.org</i>. Archived from <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.light2015.org/Home/ScienceStories/1000-Years-of-Arabic-Optics.html">the original</a> on 1 October 2014<span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">9 October</span> 2017</span>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=www.light2015.org&amp;rft.atitle=International+Year+of+Light+%E2%80%93+Ibn+Al-Haytham+and+the+Legacy+of+Arabic+Optics&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.light2015.org%2FHome%2FScienceStories%2F1000-Years-of-Arabic-Optics.html&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AIbn+al-Haytham" class="Z3988"></span>.
<link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite class="citation web cs1"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://en.unesco.org/news/international-year-light-ibn-al-haytham-pioneer-modern-optics-celebrated-unesco">"International Year of Light: Ibn al Haytham, pioneer of modern optics celebrated at UNESCO"</a>. <i>UNESCO</i>. <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20150918044445/https://en.unesco.org/news/international-year-light-ibn-al-haytham-pioneer-modern-optics-celebrated-unesco">Archived</a> from the original on 18 September 2015<span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">9 October</span> 2017</span>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=UNESCO&amp;rft.atitle=International+Year+of+Light%3A+Ibn+al+Haytham%2C+pioneer+of+modern+optics+celebrated+at+UNESCO&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fen.unesco.org%2Fnews%2Finternational-year-light-ibn-al-haytham-pioneer-modern-optics-celebrated-unesco&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AIbn+al-Haytham" class="Z3988"></span>. Specifically, he was the first to explain that vision occurs when light bounces on an object and then enters an eye. <link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFAdamson2016" class="citation book cs1">Adamson, Peter (2016). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=KEpRDAAAQBAJ"><i>Philosophy in the Islamic World: A History of Philosophy Without Any Gaps</i></a>. Oxford University Press. p.&#160;77. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-0-19-957749-1" title="Special:BookSources/978-0-19-957749-1"><bdi>978-0-19-957749-1</bdi></a>. <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20230205005719/https://books.google.com/books?id=KEpRDAAAQBAJ">Archived</a> from the original on 5 February 2023<span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">3 October</span> 2016</span>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Philosophy+in+the+Islamic+World%3A+A+History+of+Philosophy+Without+Any+Gaps&amp;rft.pages=77&amp;rft.pub=Oxford+University+Press&amp;rft.date=2016&amp;rft.isbn=978-0-19-957749-1&amp;rft.aulast=Adamson&amp;rft.aufirst=Peter&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DKEpRDAAAQBAJ&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AIbn+al-Haytham" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-Adamson_2016_77-14"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-Adamson_2016_77_14-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Adamson_2016_77_14-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFAdamson2016" class="citation book cs1">Adamson, Peter (2016). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=KEpRDAAAQBAJ"><i>Philosophy in the Islamic World: A History of Philosophy Without Any Gaps</i></a>. Oxford University Press. p.&#160;77. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-0-19-957749-1" title="Special:BookSources/978-0-19-957749-1"><bdi>978-0-19-957749-1</bdi></a>. <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20230205005719/https://books.google.com/books?id=KEpRDAAAQBAJ">Archived</a> from the original on 5 February 2023<span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">3 October</span> 2016</span>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Philosophy+in+the+Islamic+World%3A+A+History+of+Philosophy+Without+Any+Gaps&amp;rft.pages=77&amp;rft.pub=Oxford+University+Press&amp;rft.date=2016&amp;rft.isbn=978-0-19-957749-1&amp;rft.aulast=Adamson&amp;rft.aufirst=Peter&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DKEpRDAAAQBAJ&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AIbn+al-Haytham" class="Z3988"></span></span>
